sec.p:
The results of this study will be used in many different ways. Potential final dissemination strategies include:
Electronic versions of final workbook and curriculum materials;
Instructional videos to support independent action planning work;
Standardized reporting forms in partnership with the CDC-OSH to support ongoing data collection and fidelity to the training model;
Technical assistance worksheets and activities posted on www.sustaintool.org;
Webinars;
Findings about the impact of the program sustainability action planning model and training curriculum on programmatic and organizational outcomes in high-visibility cancer, public health, and dissemination and implementation science journals and conferences;
All lessons learned from the training program and a final curriculum product will be systematically disseminated to diverse audiences, since the methods and approaches are generalizable and adaptable to any public health initiative.
